HEADWORD: Croydon
<hw>Croy"don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Croydon</ets>, England.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of carriage
like a gig, orig. of wicker-work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of cotton sheeting; also, a calico.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

